"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The Shahenshah of Hindi cinema, Amitabh Bachchan, seems to be the Shahenshah on Crypto street as well as his collection of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) smashed all records in an auction. \\n  \\n The collection that included Madhushala NFTs, The Loot Box NFT, Iconic Vintage Posters NFT and BigB Punks and NFT Arts went under the hammer for $966,000 or Rs 7.18 crore, the highest ever in India. \\n  \\n The most successful was the Madhushala NFT collection - his father’s poem, recorded in the superstar\\n\\nOn the first day of Bachchan’s [auction](https://www.beyondlife.club/), which started on November 1 and ends on November 4, his NFT collections have amassed bids upwards of $520,000. Of this, the *Madhushala* collection – his late father’s poem collection recorded in the superstar’s own voice – has received bids amounting to $420,000.\\n\\n### Bollywood’s NFT dreams\\n\\nBachchan is among the first Indian stars to dabble in NFTs, but he is not the only one.\\n\\nSunny Leone recently [hosted a private NFT sale](https://www.livemint.com/market/cryptocurrency/sunny-leone-becomes-first-indian-actress-to-launch-misftiz-as-an-nft-11635851301535.html). Salman Khan [teased his NFT dreams](https://www.livemint.com/money/personal-finance/salman-khan-to-launch-his-nfts-as-blockchain-craze-grips-bollywood-11634121205602.html) on social media. The Malayalam-language crime thriller *Kurup*, which stars and is co-produced by Dulquer Salmaan, recently became the [first Indian film](https://www.news9live.com/entertainment/dulquer-salmaan-sobhita-dhulipala-kurup-nft-first-indian-film-128368) to hold an NFT sale of signed posters, videos with embedded music and digital artwork.\\n\\nBeyond films, Indian cricketer Dinesh Karthik is auctioning [a digital art reel](https://bit.ly/3m28fNc) of a match-winning shot for around $20,000. Fashion designer Manish Malhotra recently sold NFTs of [digital sketches](https://themorningcrypto.com/manish-malhotra-launches-his-first-nft-artwork/) of some of his iconic creations for [$4,000 a piece](https://www.reuters.com/business/finance/bollywood-stars-indian-celebrities-launch-nfts-amid-global-craze-2021-10-24/)\\n\\nWhile there is some excitement drumming up in the sector, no one in India – not even Bachchan – can rival the biggest NFT deals globally.\\n\\nA CryptoPunk, one of 10,000 collectible characters created by Canadian software developers Matt Hall and John Watkinson, sold for almost $12 million. American digital artist Mike Winkelmann, popularly known as Beeple, sold an NFT of his work *Everydays: the First 5000 Days* for a [staggering $69 million](https://www.theverge.com/2021/3/11/22325054/beeple-christies-nft-sale-cost-everydays-69-million) – the highest price tag for an NFT artwork to date.\",\"timestamp\":1636114361,\"title\":\"Amitabh Bachchan’s NFT collection auctioned at record $1 million\"},\"digest\":\"5UxmfuobF2tQjg7pT3G4ndRHjosIQ5V15rM8qKARpfE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xE1817bD9969013fC24Ab3CC5887f8D95b69D129e\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"3UsZOE30utZDdQuRozYHZlzYxsRPud_lCQd5YqEyLPc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"ogpUc3CPR4otFGaMeVkLxEi2H31oy-6lsA_rp2yWNW8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"o1NPRPVbsvWbyqLaK7yOKQjPS9VYrDaPQ7a1nmDcxB46Yxk5vouuDI-Owv1qdV1BypdwSfFa3NqWhzx8bW5NYg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x31d05e176e535024de359cca0b0157231ac52170321e546d1dfd5f72bfe50ca56a8557efd996bd1e8b9d9eb0a7d79dd1cfff0d804704b6bed623e92ee37396f31c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"3UsZOE30utZDdQuRozYHZlzYxsRPud_lCQd5YqEyLPc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"ogpUc3CPR4otFGaMeVkLxEi2H31oy-6lsA_rp2yWNW8\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"5UxmfuobF2tQjg7pT3G4nd